  <Subject Subject_ID="300022650">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300263898</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>video cameras [300263898], cameras by form or function [300022637], cameras (photographic equipment) [300022636], cameras and camera accessories [300022635], photographic equipment [300022633], image-making equipment [300162803], equipment by process [300024659], equipment [300122241], Tools and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300022238], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hand-held, shoulder-mounted, or structurally-attached cameras using electronic components to record or transmit motion pictures and sound for television production. Color television cameras have typically used a beam-splitter to focus onto the faces of three red, green, and blue image tubes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000094663/Kenney and Groome, Television Camera Operation According to Ritch (1987)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In de hand of op de schouder gehouden, of vast bevestigde camera's die gebruikmaken van elektronische componenten voor het opnemen of uitzenden van film en geluid voor televisieproductie. Kleurentelevisiecamera's hebben meestal een bundelsplitser om op de vlakken van de rode, groene en blauwe beeldbuis te focussen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000119919/RKD-Nederlands Instituut voor Kunstgeschiedenis [database] (2021-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Câmeras portáteis, montadas no ombro ou conectadas estruturalmente usando componentes eletrônicos para gravar ou transmitir imagens em movimento e som para produção de televisão. As câmeras de televisão em cores normalmente usam um divisor de feixe para focalizar as faces de três tubos de imagem vermelho, verde e azul.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
